        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 7:25PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 725 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Loghill Village, or 19 miles southwest of Montrose,
moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Ouray
and southeastern Montrose Counties.

This includes U.S. Highway 550 in Colorado near mile marker 122.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
